&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialty Grade Community Paediatrician post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the enthusiastic and dedicated team in Community Paediatrics at Wrexham Maelor Hospital in North Wales, for a period of 12 months covering Maternity Leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our community paediatric department has 2 office bases in Flintshire and Wrexham. We are a busy and dynamic team with a clear emphasis on delivering top quality care to our children and young people. There is a child development centre in each local authority and we work in partnership between Health, Education and Social Services. We have excellent working relationships with our nursing and acute colleagues and with our tertiary centre specialist services at Alder Hey Hospital, Liverpool as well as with Wrexham and Flintshire local authorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates with a special interest in neurodisability, neurodevelopment, safeguarding or adoption/fostering would be able to develop these areas within our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointee will provide support for inpatient and outpatient services. Duties will include assessment and management of children referred acutely via the emergency department or their general practitioner as well as providing supervision and support to less experienced, first on-call tier trainees and non-training doctors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinicians with appropriate registration or impending registration on the Specialist Register may apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details or informal visits, please contact Dr Lawrence Dixon, Community Paediatrician on 01978 727083.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
